Package: dominatR
Title: Feature Dominance-based R Package for genomic data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Simon Lizarazo [aut, cre], Rajendra KC [ctb], Kevin Van Bortle [aut, cre, cph]
Maintainer: Simon Lizarazo <silizarazoch@gmail.com>,
            Kevin Van Bortle <kvbortle@illinois.edu>
Description: 
  dominatR is an R package for quantifying and visualizing feature dominance in datasets. dominatR makes use    of Shannon's entropy to identify features that are dominated within a particular category or condition.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/VanBortleLab/dominatR
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: false
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.4.0)
Imports: dplyr, forcats,  lubridate,  purrr,  readr,  stringr,  tibble,  tidyr,  geomtextpath,  ggforce,  ggplot2,  scales,  ggnewscale, SummarizedExperiment, airway, tidyverse, BiocStyle
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
biocViews: Visualization, Normalization, Classification, GeneExpression
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
BugReports: https://github.com/VanBortleLab/dominatR/issues
VignetteBuilder: knitr
